Sentencas: Fe-doped SrMoO4 (SrMo0.94Fe0.06O4-delta), synthesized by an EDTA-glycine complexing combustion process, can be easily reduced to SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-delta (SMF) at 850 degrees C in pure H-2 atmosphere.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite for SOFC anode

Sentencas: The incorporation of Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC) into SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-delta is supposed to enhance the ionic conductivity and catalytic activity of SMF.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite for SOFC anode

Sentencas: Phase composition and chemical compatibility of SMF-GDC composite in both air and H-2 atmosphere are confirmed by X-ray diffraction test.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite for SOFC anode

Sentencas: SMF-GDC composites in different mass ratios are systematically investigated in terms of electrical conductivity, electrochemical performance and power output with the fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite for SOFC anode

Sentencas: With the addition of GDC, the ionic conductivity is able to be improved and the lowest interfacial polarization resistance is observed to be 0.647 Omega cm(2) for SMF7-GDC3 composite anode at 850 degrees C. With SMF7-GDC(3) as anode, the single cell is able to generate a maximum power density of 530 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C when fed with pure H-2 (30 mL min(-1)) and demonstrates a considerable stability with the anode exposed to H-2 and upon redox cycling.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of SrMo0.94Fe0.06O3-δ-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite for SOFC anode
